# Spec: Issues Module — RiskShield

## Objective

Add a first-class **Issues** module to RiskShield: a configurable problem log for things
that have already gone wrong and need tracking to resolution. Issues sit alongside the
existing Risk Register (future threats) and Change Register (formal scope decisions) to
close the gap for real-world, in-flight problems.

### User stories

- As a PMO user I can log an issue with a category, priority, owner, estimated cost and
  target resolution date so that nothing falls through the cracks.
- As a PMO user I can link an issue to one or more risks and/or change requests so that
  the full picture of a problem is connected.
- As a PMO user I can move an issue through Open → In Progress → Closed so that the
  register shows live status.
- As an Admin I can configure issue categories in Settings so that the module fits any
  client or industry without code changes.
- As a PMO user I can see linked issues on the Risk Detail and Change Detail pages.
- As a Read-Only user I can view the issue register and issue detail but cannot create
  or edit.

