## Service Interface

### `IssueService` (`src/api/services.ts`)

```typescript
export interface IssueService {
  list(): Promise<Issue[]>;
  get(ref: string): Promise<Issue | null>;
  create(input: IssueInput): Promise<Issue>;
  update(ref: string, patch: Partial<IssueInput>): Promise<Issue>;
  archive(ref: string): Promise<Issue>;
  restore(ref: string): Promise<Issue>;
}
```

`Services` gains `issues: IssueService`.

### REST contract (HTTP mode)

| Method | Path | Body | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/issues` | — | `Issue[]` (including archived) |
| GET | `/api/issues/:ref` | — | `Issue` |
| POST | `/api/issues` | `IssueInput` | `Issue` (server assigns ref, timestamps) |
| PATCH | `/api/issues/:ref` | `Partial<IssueInput>` | `Issue` |
| POST | `/api/issues/:ref/archive` | — | `Issue` |
| POST | `/api/issues/:ref/restore` | — | `Issue` |

Status changes (Open → In Progress → Closed) are plain `PATCH` calls with
`{ status: "..." }` — no separate transition endpoint needed.

