## Bidirectional Linking

Issues link to risks and changes. The mock layer keeps all three in sync:

```
issue.linkedRiskRefs   ↔  risk.linkedIssueRefs
issue.linkedChangeRefs ↔  change.linkedIssueRefs
```

`syncIssueLinks(issueRef, linkedRiskRefs, linkedChangeRefs)` in `mockServices.ts`
mirrors the existing `syncRiskLinks()` pattern.

The backend must enforce the same consistency on create, update and delete.

---

## Permissions

No new permissions. Issues reuse the existing RBAC model:

| Action | Permission required |
|---|---|
| View issues, register, detail | `risks:read` (issues are in-scope for any PMO reader) |
| Log, edit issues | `risks:update` |
| Archive / restore | `risks:archive` |

> Rationale: issues are operationally closer to risks than changes. Using existing
> permissions avoids a breaking change to the RBAC model and means all existing
> roles work without migration.

