## Code Style

Follow existing patterns exactly — no new libraries, no new style approaches:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — lazy route (App.tsx pattern)
const IssueRegister = lazy(() =>
  import("./pages/issues/IssueRegister").then((m) => ({ default: m.IssueRegister })),
);

// ✅ Correct — upsert pattern (AppData.tsx pattern)
const upsertIssue = useCallback((rec: Issue) =>
  setIssues((prev) => {
    const exists = prev.some((i) => i.issueReference === rec.issueReference);
    return exists
      ? prev.map((i) => (i.issueReference === rec.issueReference ? rec : i))
      : [...prev, rec];
  }), []);

// ✅ Correct — inline styles referencing CSS vars (tokens pattern)
<div style={{ color: T.brand, background: T.brandBg }}>...</div>

// ❌ Wrong — do not use Tailwind, CSS modules, or styled-components
// ❌ Wrong — do not add new npm dependencies
```

Naming:
- Files: `PascalCase.tsx` for components/pages
- Hooks: `useSomething`
- Types: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Accessors for `useSortPage`: module-level `const ACCESSORS = { ... } satisfies Record<...>`

