## Implementation Plan

### Phase A — Foundation (data layer, no UI)
*Must be done first; all UI phases depend on this.*

1. `domain.ts` — add `Issue`, `IssueInput`, `IssueStatus`; add `linkedIssueRefs` to `Risk` + `ChangeRequest`
2. `config.ts` — add `issueCategories` to `AppConfig`, `DEFAULT_CONFIG`, `sanitizeConfig`
3. `lookups.ts` — add `ISSUE_STATUSES`
4. `tokens.ts` — add `ISSUE_STATUS_STYLES`
5. `services.ts` — add `IssueService`; extend `Services`
6. `seed.ts` — add `SEED_ISSUES`; add `linkedIssueRefs: []` to existing seeds
7. `mockServices.ts` — implement `IssueService` + `syncIssueLinks()`
8. `httpServices.ts` — implement HTTP `IssueService`
9. `AppData.tsx` — add `issues` state + all mutation callbacks

**Gate:** `typecheck` + `build` pass. No UI yet.

### Phase B — Core pages
*Depend on Phase A.*

10. `IssueRegister.tsx` — register page
11. `IssueForm.tsx` — Add + Edit forms (wizard)
12. `IssueDetail.tsx` — detail page with inline status update

**Gate:** Can log, view, edit and archive an issue end-to-end.

### Phase C — Integration
*Depend on Phase B.*

13. `App.tsx` — add lazy routes
14. `Sidebar.tsx` — add Issues nav section
15. `RiskDetail.tsx` — add Linked Issues section
16. `ChangeDetail.tsx` — add Linked Issues section
17. `SettingsPage.tsx` — add `issueCategories` editor

**Gate:** Full end-to-end flow, bidirectional links visible, settings configurable.

